Text of report by corporate-owned Russian news agency Interfax

Rostov-na-Donu, 17 October: Two police employees have been shot in Groznyy, the Interfax-South news agency was told by law-enforcement agencies of the North Caucasus Federal District.

TD 
 

"On Saturday night, while carrying out operational search activities, the police employees came under fire in Groznyy's Leninskiy District. One of the policemen died on the spot, the other died on arrival at hospital," the agency's source said.

According to him, efforts are under way to find and detain the attackers.

[In a separate development in Dagestan, unidentified persons fired on the building of the Derbent Department of Internal Affairs from automatic weapons and an under-barrel grenade launcher at around 2200 gmt on 15 October, RIA Novosti news agency reported the next day. There were no casualties.]

Source: Interfax news agency, Moscow, in Russian 0324 gmt 17 Oct 10; RIA Novosti news agency, Moscow, in Russian 0440 gmt 16 Oct 10
